1 24-7-613. Permissive service credit — Gap year period service.
2 (a) A member of the Arkansas Teacher Retirement System may purchase
3 permissive service credit for one (1) or more gap years periods if the
4 member:
5 (1) The member:
6 (A) Has five (5) years of actual service in the system;
7 (B)(2) Has left his or her position as a classroom teacher
8 immediately before each nonconsecutive gap year gap period or the initial gap
9 year gap period of consecutive gap years gap periods;
10 (C)(3) Returns to his or her position as a classroom teacher
11 after one (1) or more gap years gap periods;
12 (D)(4) Accrues at least one-half (½) year of service credit
13 after returning to his or her position as a classroom teacher;
14 (E)(5) Was inactive during the gap year gap period or gap years
15 gap periods; and
16 (F)(6) Is ineligible to receive free service credit for each gap
17 year gap period under another provision of the law applicable to the system;
18 and
19 (2) Each gap year amounts to an entire fiscal year.
20 (b)(1) A member may purchase one (1) one-quarter (1/4) year of
21 permissive service credit for each one (1) gap year gap period.
22 (2) A member shall not purchase more than five (5) years of
23 permissive service credit.
24 (c) Permissive service credit for one (1) or more gap years periods
25 shall not be purchasable after a member retires from the system.
26 (d) Permissive service credit shall be credited in accordance with §
27 24-7-601.
28 (e)(1) The member shall pay the actuarial equivalent of the member's
29 benefits to the system for each one-quarter (1/4) year of permissive service
30 credit purchased.
31 (2) A year Each one-quarter (1/4) year of permissive service
32 credit that is being purchased by a member shall not become credited service
33 under the system until the actuarial equivalent of the member's benefits is
34 paid in full.
35 (f) At the member's request, a member's payment for permissive service
36 credit under this section shall be refunded if the:
